channel.title: Something to check out
channel.description:
Found some things that you probly know about but ill post anyway...
World 42 http://po2.runescape.com/runescape428.jar http://po2.runescape.com/runescape.jar http://po2.runescape.com/loader1104529562.cab http://po2.runescape.com/loader-589029650.jar http://po2.runescape.com/runescape.pack200?crc=-75502365 http://po2.runescape.com/unpackclass.jar?crc=-549807395 http://po2.runescape.com/runescape.js5?crc=-126218491
And just in case you dont belive me that these are from runescape: http://jolt3.runescape.com/loader-589029650.jar http://va8.runescape.com/loader-589029650.jar http://uk7.runescape.com/loader-589029650.jar
I found most of this after decompiling the latest Runescape client. Not sure if this will help at all or not. po2 stands for the world which happens to be one of the member worlds(I forget which one) and the http://po2.runescape.com/loader1104529562.cab and http://po2.runescape.com/loader-589029650.jar were found on the website that it opens when you go to the world. The other stuff i found after decompiling the loader.jar thing.

item.title: Something to check out
item.dc:creator: @Iamadam Iamadam
item.description:
@Iamadam wrote:

http://po2.runescape.com/runescape.jar --> Thats the runescape client
http://po2.runescape.com/loader-589029650.jar --> The runescape loader (Loads the client duh)
http://po2.runescape.com/runescape.pack200?crc=-75502365 --> One of the above (Cough guess which)
http://po2.runescape.com/unpackclass.jar?crc=-549807395 --> Stuff to unpack the js5
http://po2.runescape.com/runescape.js5?crc=-126218491 --> One of the above (Cough guess which)

item.title: Something to check out
item.dc:creator: @Cheese_Police c|p
item.description:
@Cheese_Police wrote:

the numbers after “runescape” is your session id. if you want an uber undetectable bot then you will want to emulate session ids and load it from the web, which isnt too hard to do.
